title: Quality Engine in the Correct weight for the engine
description: My car is an older car with 100,000 miles. The engine of my car was built for 10/40 oil which is no longer carried in filling stations. Dont let mechanics and the oil changing stations tell you that 15/30 or any other weight oil will be OK. It's not true. Buy 10/40 and take it you when changing the oil
